    "recap_headline": "The University of Texas at Austin Athletics",
    "recap_text": "AUBURN, Ala. \u2014\nWith No. 2 Texas two outs away from taking the series opener, No. 5 Auburn cleared the bases to notch a 4-3 walk-off win\u00a0at Plainsman Park on Friday night.\nBristol Carter delivered a two-run single and the Tigers (19-3, 4-0 SEC) capitalized on a defensive miscue to secure their 12\nth\nstraight victory.\nIn the defeat,\nAiden Robbins\nmounted his first career multi-homer performance, smacking a game-tying blast in the fourth and a go-ahead solo shot in final frame.\nRobbins' ninth-inning jack marked his eighth home run in his first 83 at-bats at Texas (18-3, 2-2 SEC), setting a new career high.\nAuburn southpaw Garrett Brewer (1-1) logged the win, while Longhorn left-hander\nEthan Walker\n(1-1) was tagged with the loss.\nIn a pitchers' duel among the top two staffs in the league, Texas starter\nRuger Riojas\ntossed a season-long 6 1/3 innings of one-run baseball.\nAfter surrendering back-to-back doubles to open his outing, Riojas retired 20 of the next 21 batters he faced. The righty finished with six strikeouts across a season-high 99 pitches.\nOn the other side, Jake Marciano threw seven innings, yielding one run on Robbins' fourth-inning homer. Marciano totaled nine punchouts, limiting the Longhorns to two hits and a pair of free passes.\nTexas will look to even the series on Saturday. First pitch is slated for 6 p.m. at Plainsman Park.",
